1. Edit the Ceph configuration file:

Locate and open your Ceph configuration file (usually /etc/ceph/ceph.conf).

2. Add or modify the rbd_default_features setting:

Add the following line within the [global] section of the configuration file or modify it if it already exists:

Code
 
   rbd_default_features = 125

The value 125 corresponds to the feature bits for exclusive-lock (1), object-map (4), fast-diff (8), and journaling (128), according to Ceph documentation. 

Restart Ceph Monitors: After modifying the configuration file, you need to restart the Ceph monitors for the changes to take effect. You can do this by running: 

Code
 
   sudo systemctl restart ceph-mon.*
 
